org.apache.sshd.common

Interface FactoryManager

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ChannelListenerManager, KexFactoryManager, KeyPairProviderHolder, PropertyResolver, SessionListenerManager, SignatureFactoriesManager
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ClientFactoryManager, ServerFactoryManager
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFactoryManager, SshClient, SshServer

    public interface FactoryManager
extends KexFactoryManager, SessionListenerManager, ChannelListenerManager, PropertyResolver
    This interface allows retrieving all the NamedFactory used in the SSH protocol.
    Author:
    Apache MINA SSHD Project

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • IGNORE_MESSAGE_FREQUENCY

        static final String IGNORE_MESSAGE_FREQUENCY
        Average number of packets to be skipped before an SSH_MSG_IGNORE message is inserted in the stream. If non-positive, then feature is disabled
        See Also:
        IGNORE_MESSAGE_VARIANCE, Constant Field Values

      • DEFAULT_IGNORE_MESSAGE_FREQUENCY

        static final long DEFAULT_IGNORE_MESSAGE_FREQUENCY
        Default value of IGNORE_MESSAGE_FREQUENCY if none set.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • IGNORE_MESSAGE_VARIANCE

        static final String IGNORE_MESSAGE_VARIANCE
        The variance to be used around the configured IGNORE_MESSAGE_FREQUENCY value in order to avoid insertion at a set frequency. If zero, then exact frequency is used. If negative, then the absolute value is used. If greater or equal to the frequency, then assumed to be zero - i.e., no variance
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DEFAULT_IGNORE_MESSAGE_VARIANCE

        static final int DEFAULT_IGNORE_MESSAGE_VARIANCE
        Default value for IGNORE_MESSAGE_VARIANCE if none configured
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • IGNORE_MESSAGE_SIZE

        static final String IGNORE_MESSAGE_SIZE
        Minimum size of SSH_MSG_IGNORE payload to send if feature enabled. If non-positive then no message is sent. Otherwise, the actual size is between this size and twice its value
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        Value of IGNORE_MESSAGE_SIZE if none configured
        See Also:
